  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6<br /><br />Boil a full kettle<br /><br />Peel the <strong>potatoes </strong>and chop them into large, bite-sized pieces<br /><br />Top, tail and chop the <strong>courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into quarters lengthways, then chop into large bite-sized pieces<br /><br /><br /></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat<br /><br />Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender<br /><br />Once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">While the potatoes are cooking, slice the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8]</span> wedges</span><br /><br />Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) the <strong>garlic cloves</strong><br /><br />Trim, then slice the <strong>spring onions</strong><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped courgette</strong> to a tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Squeeze over the <strong>juice</strong> of 1 <span class=\"text-danger\">[2]</span> <strong>lemon wedge<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></span></p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 8-10 min or until golden</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive </strong><strong>oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\n<p>Pat the <strong>cod fillets</strong> dry with <strong>kitchen paper</strong> and season them with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong><br /><br />Once hot, add the <strong>cod fillets</strong> to the pan and cook for 2 min on each side</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong>, the <strong>juice</strong> of 1 <span class=\"text-danger\">[2]</span> <strong>lemon wedge<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and 30g <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span> of <strong>butter</strong> to the pan and cook for 2 min further until the cod is cooked through and the butter has melted</span><br /><br />Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, return the <strong>drained potatoes</strong> to a low heat with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a splash of <strong>milk</strong></p>\n<p>Season with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and mash until smooth</p>\n<p>Once smooth, stir through the <strong>chopped spring onions</strong> – this is your <strong>champ</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2374R2374v2Step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pan-fried</strong> <strong>cod</strong> over the<strong> champ</strong> with the <strong>roast courgette</strong> to the side<br /><br /><span class=\"text-highlight\">Spoon over the <strong>garlic butter </strong>and garnish with the <strong>remaining</strong></span><strong><span class=\"text-highlight\"> lemon wedges</span><br /><br /></strong>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
